parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate lubrication of the front axle can cause the front wheels to lock up while driving, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Low Fluid Levels
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Low transmission fluid levels can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, difficulty shifting, and even complete failure.
symptoms: Vehicle does not move or pull when pressing the gas pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the transmission case can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, difficulty shifting, and even complete failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Lock-up due to Transmission Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning transmission can cause the front end to lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Front end locks up while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning seat belts can fail to restrain passengers in the event of an accident, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Seat belts do not catch or stop when pulled abruptly
rear seat belts do not retract properly
front seat belts fail to hold driver/passenger in place during a collision

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The hood does not stay latched
the hood is loose or rattles
the hood latch is broken or damaged.
